<a href="#business-update" name="business-update"></a><table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="full-block" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" ><table cellpadding="40" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="middle" class="text-block" style="padding-bottom:10px; color:#666666; font-size:13px; line-height:22px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="business-update-title" style="padding-bottom:20px; " ><img style="display: block;" src="http://connect.pivotal.io/rs/625-IUJ-009/images/rita-nl-portrait.png" alt="Rita" align="right"> <span style="color: #666666; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px;">BUSINESS UPDATE</span><br> <span style="margin: 0; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 24px; text-transform: uppercase;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-e92b2559-666f-865e-a4db-7277f3e67c7d"><span>Analyst Relations as Continuous Conversation</span><span> </span></span></span><br> <span style="color: #666666; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px;">Rita Manachi, Analyst Relations Lead</span></div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="top" class="stack" style="color:#666666; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; padding-bottom:20px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="business-update-entry" >
<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-e92b2559-6670-69b0-0eee-8c179a7ffddd"> </span></p>
<p class="normal">Not too long ago, I had the opportunity to introduce myself <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://sites.google.com/a/pivotal.io/inside-pivotal/newsletters/pivotal-newsletter-february-12-2016#my-name-is">in this newsletter</a>.
    In case you forgot, the short version is that I'm Rita Manachi and I lead Analyst Relations&mdash;or AR&mdash;for Pivotal.
    I joined the Pivotal team in November, but we've done so much since then that it feels like I've been here much longer! <br /><br /> Since that time we've held close to 40 briefings with analysts, covering Pivotal Cloud Foundry and the Pivotal Big Data Suite, and I attended two Gartner events with my colleagues in product management and product marketing.
     <br /><br /> The umbrella goal for AR is to help Pivotal sales by increasing the visibility of Pivotal among industry analysts such as <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://www.forrester.com/">Forrester</a>, <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.gartner.com/">Gartner</a>, <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" 
href="https://451research.com/">The 451</a>, etc.
    If I have anything like a "philosophy" for analyst relations, it's to achieve a continuity of conversation.
    That is, interactions with analysts are not one-off events, but part of an ongoing dialogue between us, them, and importantly, our customers.
    Customers validate our value, and analysts influence the purchasing decisions of those customers.
    This is how we inform their perspective on Pivotal, and the market as a whole.
    If that conversation atrophies, so does our influence with customers.
    <br /><br /> So, how does analyst relations help Pivotal sales? At the most basic level, we educate analysts about our products, services, and value proposition.
    More broadly, we influence their views of the software infrastructure/middleware landscape, and that influences how they advise customers and the industry about us and our respective markets.
    But most importantly, customers who validate our value proposition and evince that we're industry leaders are the bedrock of validation!  <br /><br /> Understanding that this is not a one-way dialogue is a great way to help us help you.
    We improve through information&mdash;including information that you share with us.
    Finally, I'm happy to share with you our MVP 're-do' of the <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://sites.google.com/a/pivotal.io/inside-pivotal/departments/analyst-relations">AR site on Inside Pivotal</a>.
 It's easier to find, and easier to navigate.
    And let me know how we're doing!  Find me at: <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="mailto:rmanachi@pivotal.io">rmanachi@pivotal.io</a> or <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="mailto:analystrelations@pivotal.io">analystrelations@pivotal.io</a>.</p>
</div>
