<a href="#agile-update" name="agile-update"></a><table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="full-block" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" ><table cellpadding="40" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="middle" class="text-block" style="padding-bottom:10px; color:#666666; font-size:13px; line-height:22px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="agile-update-title" style="padding-bottom:20px; " ><img style="display: block;" src="http://connect.pivotal.io/rs/625-IUJ-009/images/nl-portrait-dburkes.png" alt="Danny Burkes" align="right"> <span style="color: #666666; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px;">AGILE UPDATE</span><br> <span style="margin: 0; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 24px; text-transform: uppercase;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-e92b2559-6671-674d-5341-68b630d91b08"><span>Tokyo Agile</span></span></span><br> <span style="color: #666666; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px;">Danny Burkes, Office Director, Tokyo</span></div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="top" class="stack" style="color:#666666; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; padding-bottom:20px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="agile-update-entry" >
<p class="normal">Hello from Tokyo! I'm Danny Burkes, Director of the new Pivotal Labs practice here.
  Tokyo is one of the newest Labs locations&mdash;officially opening our doors on September 1, 2015&mdash;and is the first Pivotal Labs location in APJ.
    <br /><br /> We're here because we see a substantial demand from large Japanese enterprises, across many domains, for transformational relationships to help these companies build in-house product and development expertise.
  Many of our clients currently outsource those capabilities.
   We're addressing these requests with a typical go-slow approach, proving results through an initial engagement, and moving on to a deeper, broader relationship.
  We're in the early stages of that now with a few companies, and I'm confident that with the team that we have in Japan&mdash;both in Labs and the larger Pivotal presence&mdash;we'll have a great many success stories to tell.
  <br /><br /> We started with three developers, a product manager, and a product designer, all from existing Labs locations around the world.
  We added five developers, two product managers, and two product designers, all Tokyo residents&mdash;some Japanese, and others internationals who have lived and worked in Tokyo for some time.
   <br /><br /> We now have fourteen billable Pivots, capable of taking on up to three simultaneous projects, with a plan to increase that to twenty-one by the end of 2016.
  Our first project was a fin-tech engagement with a major systems integrator whose niche was providing services to small and mid-sized banks.
  Based on the success of that engagement, we are expecting them to return in Q2 for a longer, more enablement-focused engagement.
  <br /><br /> An engagement with Japan's largest air carrier, All Nippon Airlines (ANA), followed.
  They have an ambitious multi-year plan to reimagine and the entire customer experience digitally&mdash;from web to mobile&mdash;and we've helped to start building a new iOS app.
  That was really a "try before you buy" engagement, but our effectiveness has made us very hopeful that they'll return somewhere in Q2, for a longer engagement.
  We think we can be their principal partner in both product definition and development, on all their platforms.
  We're excited about this! They have the potential to become both the anchor client for Labs Tokyo and a critical case study that can establish our leadership in the Japanese market.
  <br /><br /> <img src="http://connect.pivotal.io/rs/625-IUJ-009/images/agileupdate1v4n4.png" alt="eating sestina-maki" width="500" /><br /><img src="http://connect.pivotal.io/rs/625-IUJ-009/images/agileupdate2v4n4.png" alt="Tokyo office" width="500" /><br /><em><span style="font-size: 10px;">Scenes from Roppongi Hills (from top to bottom): Eating setsuban-maki to celebrate launch; Inception 
with new clients.</span></em> <br /><br /> We're plugged into the tech community.
  We recently held an agile enablement session with our EMC colleagues, and ran meet-up to a packed house on <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.slideshare.net/makingx/spring-cloud-netflix">Spring Cloud for Netflix</a>.
   <br /><br /> The greatest part of Pivotal for me, has been without fail, the remarkably talented and caring people that I've worked with over the years.
  I'm happy to say that the spirit of what we do, and how we do it, is being repeated here in Tokyo!</p>
</div>
