<a href="#my-name-is" name="my-name-is"></a><table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="full-block" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" ><table cellpadding="40" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="middle" class="text-block" style="padding-bottom:10px; color:#666666; font-size:13px; line-height:22px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="my-name-is-title" style="padding-bottom:20px; " ><img style="display: block;" src="http://connect.pivotal.io/rs/625-IUJ-009/images/michaelgresham-nl-portrait.png" alt="Michael" align="right"> <span style="color: #666666; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px;">MY NAME IS...</span><br> <span style="margin: 0; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 24px; text-transform: uppercase;">Michael Gresham</span><br> <span style="color: #666666; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px;">Michael Gresham, Product Manager, Cloud Foundry</span></div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="top" class="stack" style="color:#666666; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; padding-bottom:20px; " ><span style="font-size:20px;">At Pivotal I&hellip;</span><div class="mktEditable" id="at-pivotal-i" style="padding-top:10px; " >Am the product manager for Apps Manager, PCF and PWS's developer portal.</div>
<br>
<span style="font-size:20px;">You can find me&hellip;</span><div class="mktEditable" id="you-can-find-me" style="padding-top:10px; " >Swiveling around on my Fluidstance balance board on the 4th floor of the SF office, near the elevators. I'm usually wearing Billionaire Boys Club or Ice Cream shirts, except for days when I have my Pivotal swag on. If not swiveling, I'm losing at ping-pong, but looking like a pro doing it.</div>
<br>
<span style="font-size:20px;">Currently, I am working on&hellip;</span><div class="mktEditable" id="currently-i-am" style="padding-top:10px; " >An in-place React JS rewrite of Apps Manager. We call it NBA JAM (New, Better, All-Javascript Apps Manager). Coincidentally, I'm pretty good with backronyms.</div>
<br>
<span style="font-size:20px;">In my spare time&hellip;</span><div class="mktEditable" id="in-my-spare-time" style="padding-top:10px; " >I'm an indie game developer currently working on my first game, Spells—a magical word game that will hopefully see the light of day (and lots of IAP conversion) in Q2 of this year. If you like word games, you should be a beta tester.  <br><br> When I'm not running a one-man game shop, I'm usually traveling to see my wife, Eva. Her job moves her around quite a bit—it's not as hard as you might think because they help pay for us to travel to see each other. I got to live in Buenos Aires, Argentina with her for about a month last year!<img src="http://connect.pivotal.io/rs/625-IUJ-009/images/hellomynameis2v4n4.jpg" alt="on horseback" width="500"><br><em><span style="font-size: 10px;">Mike and wife horseback riding in the Mendoza hills in Argentina.</span></em></div>
<br>
<span style="font-size:20px;">Something you probably don’t know about me&hellip;</span><div class="mktEditable" id="something-you-dont-know" style="padding-top:10px; " >I minored in Japanese in college. Nowadays I only talk to myself in Japanese, so it's pretty bad. But always looking to get better (again). I'm also REALLY into cars and I've taken some pretty great exotics out on the track, as well as followed the last leg of the Gumball 3000 through Death Valley Last year.<img src="http://connect.pivotal.io/rs/625-IUJ-009/images/hellomynameis1v4n4.jpg" alt="gumboil 3000 rally" width="500"><br><em><span style="font-size: 10px;">Deadmau5, Tommy Lee, Lewis Hamilton, the Meow-Clarens (white with hearts), David Heinnemeir Hannson's one-off Koenniegsegg Agera HH (blue), and your author in Death Valley during the Gumball 3000 rally last year. It was about 4x as awesome as it looks.</span></em></div>
<br>
<span style="font-size:20px;">To me Pivotal&hellip;</span><div class="mktEditable" id="to-me-pivotal" style="padding-top:10px; " >Really changing the way the world builds software! I have been in love with the process since I interviewed here, and it's great to come to work every day knowing that customers large and small are using our process and our platform to transform and deliver tons more value to their customers.</div>
